Cats are carnivores and typically eat small animals such as mice, birds, and insects. They also enjoy a variety of foods such as canned cat food, dry kibble, and treats.

Cats are obligate carnivores, meaning that they are true carnivores and must eat a diet of primarily animal-based proteins and fats in order to survive and thrive. Their diet should consist of high-quality, meat-based proteins such as chicken, beef, and fish.
